description:
I started taking photos of the subject in the second half of the winter and it took a long time due to the weather to collect the pictures. One of my most cozy pastimes was to spot it with the new binoculars while this photo was taken.

I thought of publishing the image in full cutout, but somehow the location of the stars was attacked by a feeling that a huge star city moving there in vast outer space filled me almost endlessly, with a slightly strange feeling, so I left the field of view.

The color of the galaxies I feel can be brought out well, but the picture isn’t really good heavens, though it was made, but the situation was mostly done for this, which I don’t care so much about. The experience is more, health is a great treasure.
:)
imaging_telescopes: Skywatcher Quattro 200/800 modified carbon Skywatcher 200/800 Pro Carbon
title: Messier 106 and its surroundings
